The term \u201Cbig tech\u201D usually refers to a group of nine tech companies whose market capitalization exceeds $200 billion or has grown rapidly in recent years: Amazon, Apple, Facebook, Google parent Alphabet (the parent company of Google), Netflix, Tesla, Alibaba Group (the parent company of Ali Baba), and Microsoft.`))}MDXContent.isMDXComponent=!0;

